Paper: hep-th/9809115

Date: 1998-09-16

Title: Path Integral for the Dirac Equation

Comments: 4 pages, uses sprocl.sty, talk delivered at the the conference

"Path-integrals from peV to TeV", Florence, August, 1998Journal-ref: Phys.Lett. B453 (1999) 40-45

A path integral representation is given for the solutions of the 3+1dimensional Dirac equation. The regularity of the trajectories, thenon-relativistic limit and the semiclassical approximation are brieflymentioned.